article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 67, Cal Poly-SLO 40
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Shane Edwards and Matt Mouzy scored 15 points apiece to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 67-40 season-opening victory over Cal Poly on Friday night. John Fowler added 12 points and Mouzy was 3-for-6 from three-point range for the Trojans (1-0), who connected on 6 of 12 3-pointers in the game. Titus Shelton scored 15 points and David Hanson pulled down seven rebounds for the Mustangs (0-1).
